1 Sec. 7. Section 71-567, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 71-567 (1)(a) No later than December 31, 2024, the council shall
4 compile the findings and recommendations under the Alzheimer's Disease
5 and Other Dementia Support Act and submit them as a State Alzheimer's
6 Plan to the Legislature and the Governor.
7 (b) No later than December 31, 2028, and every Every four years
8 thereafter, the council shall issue an updated State Alzheimer's Plan
9 addressing the items in sections 71-565 and 71-566 and any other issues
10 the council deems necessary and relevant toward addressing Alzheimer's
11 disease and dementia in Nebraska.
12 (2) By October 1 of each year after the creation of the State
13 Alzheimer's Plan, the council shall electronically submit to the
14 Legislature and the Governor an annual report on the status of
15 implementation of the State Alzheimer's Plan recommendations and any
16 barriers to implementation.
17 Sec. 8. The Aging, Alzheimer's, and Dementia Advisory Council Fund
18 is created. The fund shall consist of federal funds and grants or gifts
19 for the purposes authorized by the Aging, Alzheimer's, and Dementia
20 Support Act. Expenditures from the fund shall be subject to any
21 conditions agreed upon for receiving such funds, grants, or gifts. Such
22 funds, grants, or gifts shall be remitted to the State Treasurer for
23 credit to the fund. Any money in the fund available for investment shall
24 be invested by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska
25 Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
26 Sec. 9. Section 71-814, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
27 amended to read:
28 71-814 (1) The State Advisory Committee on Mental Health and
29 Substance Use Services is created. Members of the committee shall have a
30 demonstrated interest and commitment and specialized knowledge,
31 experience, or expertise relating to the provision of mental health
-9-

LB845 LB845
2026 2026
1 services in the State of Nebraska. The committee shall consist of twenty-
2 three members appointed by the Governor as follows: (a) One regional
3 governing board member, (b) one regional administrator, (c) twelve
4 consumers of behavioral health services or their family members, (d) two
5 providers of behavioral health services, (e) two representatives from the
6 State Department of Education, including one representative from the
7 Division of Vocational Rehabilitation of the State Department of
8 Education, (f) three representatives from the Department of Health and
9 Human Services representing mental health, social services, and medicaid,
10 (g) one representative from the Nebraska Commission on Law Enforcement
11 and Criminal Justice, and (h) one representative from the Housing Office
12 of the Community and Rural Development Division of the Department of
13 Economic Development.
14 (2) The committee shall be responsible to the division and shall (a)
15 serve as the state's mental health planning council as required by Public
16 Law 102-321, (b) conduct regular meetings, (c) provide advice and
17 assistance to the division relating to the provision of mental health
18 services and, beginning July 1, 2026, substance use disorder services in
19 the State of Nebraska, including, but not limited to, the development,
20 implementation, provision, and funding of organized peer support
21 services, (d) promote the interests of consumers and their families,
22 including, but not limited to, their inclusion and involvement in all
23 aspects of services design, planning, implementation, provision,
24 education, evaluation, and research, (e) provide reports as requested by
25 the division, and (f) engage in such other activities as directed or
26 authorized by the division.
27 (3) Beginning July 1, 2026, the State Advisory Committee on Mental
28 Health and Substance Use Services shall also perform the duties of the
29 State Advisory Committee on Substance Abuse Services.
30 Sec. 10. Section 81-6,122, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
31 amended to read:
-10-

