1 81-6,122 (1) The Department of Health and Human Services shall, in
2 collaboration with the Department of Correctional Services, the
3 Department of Economic Development, the Department of Labor, the
4 Department of Transportation, the Department of Veterans' Affairs, the
5 State Department of Education, the University of Nebraska, and the Equal
6 Opportunity Commission, develop a comprehensive strategic plan for
7 providing services to qualified persons with disabilities in the most
8 integrated community-based settings pursuant to the Olmstead decision.
9 (2) The chief executive officer of the Department of Health and
10 Human Services shall convene a team to:
11 (a) Develop the strategic plan described in subsection (1) of this
12 section;
13 (b) Appoint and convene a stakeholder advisory committee to assist
14 in the review and development of the strategic plan, such committee
15 members to include a representative from the State Advisory Committee on
16 Mental Health and Substance Use Services, the Advisory Committee on
17 Developmental Disabilities, the Nebraska Statewide Independent Living
18 Council, the Nebraska Planning Council on Developmental Disabilities, the
19 Division of Rehabilitation Services in the State Department of Education,
20 the Public Service Commission, the Commission for the Deaf and Hard of
21 Hearing, the Commission for the Blind and Visually Impaired, a housing
22 authority in a city of the first or second class and a housing authority
23 in a city of the primary or metropolitan class, the Assistive Technology
24 Partnership, the protection and advocacy system for Nebraska, an
25 assisted-living organization, the behavioral health regions, mental
26 health practitioners, developmental disability service providers, an
27 organization that advocates for persons with developmental disabilities,
28 an organization that advocates for persons with mental illness, an
29 organization that advocates for persons with brain injuries, and an area
30 agency on aging, and including two persons with disabilities representing
31 self-advocacy organizations, and, at the department’s discretion, other
-11-

LB845 LB845
2026 2026
1 persons with expertise in programs serving persons with disabilities;
2 (c) Arrange for consultation with an independent consultant to
3 assist with the continued analysis and revision of the strategic plan and
4 determine whether the benchmarks, deadlines, and timeframes are in
5 substantial compliance with the strategic plan;
6 (d) Provide continuing analysis of the strategic plan and a report
7 on the progress of the strategic plan and changes or revisions to the
8 Legislature by December 15, 2021, and every three years thereafter; and
9 (e) Provide the completed strategic plan to the Legislature and the
10 Governor by December 15, 2019.
11 (3) The reports and completed plan shall be submitted electronically
12 to the Legislature.
13 Sec. 11. Section 81-2205, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
14 amended to read:
15 81-2205 Council Committee shall mean the Aging, Alzheimer's, and
16 Dementia Advisory Council Division of Medicaid and Long-Term Care
17 Advisory Committee on Aging.
18 Sec. 12. Section 81-2212, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
19 amended to read:
20 81-2212 The council In addition to duties enumerated in section
21 68-1104, the committee shall advise the department regarding:
22 (1) The state plan on aging as developed and prepared by the
23 department;
24 (2) Policies adopted by the department;
25 (3) The needs of the state's older individuals;
26 (4) The development of the state plan and policies which affect the
27 state's older individuals;
28 (5) Such rules, regulations, and standards as may be adopted by the
29 department; and
30 (6) A community aging services budget for submission to the
31 Legislature by the department.
